File: Lukhanyo Am of Sharks challenged by Jesse Kriel of Bulls during a match. BackpagePix/Samuel Shivambu DURBAN - Sharks centre Lukhanyo Am is back at Kings Park. The 28-year-old has been playing in Japan with Kobelco Steelers on a short two-month stint and returns to join the Sharks URC team to face Ulster on Friday. The World Cup winning outside centre has signed a contract extension to remain at Kings Park for the next three years. Am returns to the Sharks squad that includes Lionel Cronje as the latest signing.